news.title: Mahindra World City Developers transfers 9.24 acres land to Alliance Budget Housing
news.para: Mahindra World City Developers has transferred land admeasuring 9.24 acres on perpetual lease within the Mahindra World City, Chennai to Alliance Budget Housing

news.title: Godrej Properties increases its stake in Wonder City Buildcon and Godrej Home Constructions
news.para: Pursuant to the said acquisition, Wonder City Buildcon and Godrej Home Constructions have become subsidiaries of Godrej Properties with effect from March 29, 2023.

news.title: TVS Emerald and HDFC Capital create Rs 1,000 crore platform for plotted development projects
news.para: Sriram Iyer, President & CEO of TVS Emerald said, "This is a strategic tie-up to grow our plotted development portfolio in the South markets."

news.title: Mangaluru civic body cuts property tax to reduce people's burden
news.para: This information will be shared to property owners through SMS,” he said, adding that 32,407 property owners have already paid property tax to the tune of Rs 17.25 crore for 2023-24. J

news.title: Chennai civic body proposes 20% discount to property tax defaulters
news.para: The GCC's offer, however, comes with some riders. Defaulters can avail themselves of the discount only if they clear the dues at one go, that too within three months of the council adopting a resolution in that regard.

news.title: Jaipur civic body to develop mobile app for urban development tax collection
news.para: ​Mayor Somya Gurjar during a review meeting instructed officials to develop the application so that residents can pay the tax easily which will also increase revenue for the corporation.

news.title: Now, Nagpur improvement trust reduces building sanction charges by 50%
news.para: The board met on Tuesday and also approved the budget for 2023-24. This was the third consecutive budget presented by NIT chairman Manoj Kumar Suryawanshi.

news.title: Nearly 1,000 properties registered daily in Indore
news.para: Revenues from property registrations until March 28 with three days left for month end have already touched Rs 250 crore, according to the registrar office hoping to conclude the last month of the financial year near about Rs 350 crore.

news.title: Pinterest to reduce office spaces as part of restructuring
news.para: US companies from technology to finance have stepped up cost cuts as they brace for a potential recession. Pinterest said it expected to incur between $100 million and $125 million in charges related to the restructuring plan.

news.title: Maharashtra: Homebuyers can access all project details with QR code
news.para: ​The Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) has started assigning QR codes to the registration certificates of developers across the state.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC's air pollution control plan rests on builder self-certification
news.para: Civic action will follow if builders fail to self-certify that a construction site meets dust mitigation guidelines like erecting metal sheets around the periphery of construction sites, water-fogging during excavation and loading/unloading construction material and sprinkling of soil strata from time to time before excavation starts.

news.title: Haryana-RERA resolved only 50% plaints in five years; buyers say 'too slow'
news.para: Homebuyers have claimed that resolution of complaints before HRera was too slow, forcing many to approach other authorities for justice.

news.title: Can't force buyer to take late flat possession: Punjab RERA
news.para: Ajay Pal Singh, member, Rera, while giving relief to Panchkula residents Niklesh Dubey and Anuja Dubey, directed "Sushma Chandigarh Grande" housing society in Zirakpur to refund the flat booking amount along with interest in addition to harassment charges.

news.title: Sunac China reaches restructuring deal with offshore creditor group
news.para: Sunac, one of the biggest property developers in China, is among the many that defaulted last year as the sector reeled under a debt crisis.

news.title: Chennai: Property tax keeps the cash flowing
news.para: While the corporation projected a deficit of `788.5 crore for financial year 2022-23, the actual deficit fell further to 517.6 crore.
